Operation Dudula in Durban says its ready to grow the organisation all over KwaZulu-Natal. The group launched its branch with a march to the eThekwini home affairs offices and a local police station. eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu reports. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Operation Dudula in Durban says it's ready to grow the organisation all over KwaZulu-Natal. The group launched its branch with a march to the eThekwini Home Affairs offices and a local police station. It is demanding police cooperate to tackle undocumented foreigners and drugs in the area. eNCA’s Lindokuhle Xulu shares more details in the video above.